2 Garlic
1 packet Jasmine rice
1 Capsicum
1 sachet Chilli Flakes
1 sachet Sesame Seeds
250 g Beef Mince
1 Carrot
1 packet Mild Thai Red Curry Paste
1 Asian Greens
1 drizzle olive oil
tbs brown sugar
plant-based butter
soy sauce
water

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the plant-based butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat. Cook half the garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and a generous pinch of salt to the pan and bring to the boil.
• Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice capsicum.
• Roughly chop Asian greens.
• Thinly slice carrot into half-moons.
• In a small bowl, combine mild Thai red curry paste, the soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, and a splash of water. Set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
• Toast sesame seeds, tossing, until golden, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook capsicum and carrot, tossing, until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and remaining garlic and cook until wilted and fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Transfer to a bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook beef mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add mild Thai red curry mixture and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

• Divide garlic rice, mild plant-based mince Thai red curry and veggie stir-fry between bowls.
• Garnish with toasted sesame seeds and chilli flakes (if using) to serve. Enjoy!